[1] Kerala wilt - coconut palm: impact
Date: Sun 11 Oct 2009
Source: Express Buzz [edited]
<http://www.expressbuzz.com/edition/story.aspx?Title=Toddy+sector+reeling+under+crisis&artid=YMS78egatiU=&SectionID=1ZkF/jmWuSA=&MainSectionID=1ZkF/jmWuSA=&SEO=&SectionName=X7s7i%7CxOZ5Y=>


Toddy sector reeling under crisis
---------------------------------
Toddy [fermented palm wine] tappers in Alappuzha district [Kerala state]
are left literally "jobless" due to various diseases affecting coconut
trees. These diseases have weakened the health and vitality of coconut
trees. Many holidaymakers hit the area to taste the toddy.

Toddy tapping is a major source of income for many. Out of the 3000-odd
toddy tappers working in the district, over 760 work in the Kuttanad
region. However, diseases like 'lethal yellowing', which has affected the
trees, have prompted many to leave.

Toddy from Kuttanad was transported [previously] to other districts, now
not even the district's requirement can be met. Tapping was a blessing to
the ailing coconut farmers who were reeling under dipping coconut prices
and the disease "mandari" [eriophyid mite] which badly hurt the coconut market.

[byline: Sajimon PS]

